pageContext.remarks: Given to Major Fisher's father by Mr. Pinfold, who formerly owned the property on which they were dug or ploughed up some years ago at Rodborough near Stroud. They were buried at no great depth in a piece of ancient woodland forming the fringe of Rodborough Common.
